JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa recorded a budget surplus of nearly R23 billion ($1.69 billion) in December, the ninth month of the 2016/17 financial year, compared with a more than R32 billion surplus over the same period in 2015/16, Treasury data showed on Monday.The table below shows revenue and expenditure for December, compared with the previous financial year. These are also expressed as a percentage of the 2016/17 budget target and the preliminary outcome for 2015/16.&nbsp; ($1 = R13.6185)